Recommend the most suitable vacancy.
When choosing a vacancy, you should use its description and work experience requirements.
If the requirements in the vacancy prescribe a completely different technology stack, then the vacancy is considered unsuitable.
If the requirements in the vacancy prescribe a smaller technology stack, then the vacancy is considered suitable.
When choosing a vacancy, you should consider the applicant's interests.

To determine the most suitable vacancy, the program will do the following:
- Perform a selection by the most relevant stack, taking into account the applicant's interests.
- Sort the selected vacancies according to the level of relevance
- Recommend the 15 most suitable vacancies

